      "name": "Relative hemolysis index sweep across 5 flow-speed operating points",
      "description": "A parametric sweep of the CFD model was executed across all five flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. Predicted RH values ranged from 0.71 to 0.94, remaining below the acceptance threshold of 1.0 at every operating point. The simulation resolves the Lagrangian particle stress-accumulation integral with sub-1% numerical uncertainty, and the hemolysis power-law constants were drawn from the published Morrison et al. (2023) calibration dataset. The authors argue that the high-fidelity nature of the simulation, combined with the calibrated damage model, renders the result functionally equivalent to a bench experiment for the purposes of this credibility assessment.",
      "quantitativeResult": "RH_max = 0.94 (operating point 3, 4.5 L/min, 3200 RPM); all five points satisfy RH < 1.0",
